# Gather PRD (Condensed)

## Product

**Gather** — Social scheduling + event discovery platform. Solves "we should hang" coordination for friend groups via: (1) social calendar + availability matching, (2) weighted algorithm for optimal meeting windows, (3) hyperlocal event discovery map.

**Target:** Urban friend groups 18–40, tier-1 North American cities (initial: Toronto). **Revenue:** B2B event partnership (Cost Per RSVP), sponsored listings.

## MVP Phases

**Phase 1 (Sprint 1–2):** Auth, social graph, manual availability grid, groups, weighted matching algorithm, smart nudges, manual event planning.

**Phase 2:** Calendar integration — Google OAuth, Microsoft Graph, Apple EventKit. Enhanced algorithm with learned preferences.

**Phase 3:** Event discovery — Eventbrite/Ticketmaster APIs, B2B partner feed, Mapbox map, one-tap RSVP.

**Phase 4:** Gamification (leaderboards, streaks), B2B portal, polish.

## Core Features (MVP)

- **Auth:** Email + OAuth (Google, Apple, Microsoft). Profile, privacy tiers.
- **Social graph:** Friend search, invitations (7-day expiry), relationship tags, block/unfriend, free/busy visibility.
- **Manual availability:** Drag-select grid, weekly blocks, export.
- **Groups:** Create/join, admin preferences, member availability, archive.
- **Availability algorithm:** Weighted scoring (friends free, event relevance, recency). Under 500ms for 10 members, 4-week horizon.
- **Smart nudges:** Availability match, event recommendation, streak warning. Max 2x/week per group.
- **Manual event planning:** Propose time, see who's free (green/yellow/red), comments, auto-finalize at 70% or 7 days.

## Data Models (Prisma)

User, Session, Friendship, Group, GroupMember, CalendarConnection, FreeBusyBlock. Enums: FriendshipStatus, GroupRole, CalendarProvider, FreeBusySource.

## Acceptance Criteria Patterns

- Sign-up &lt;2 min, OAuth scopes minimal (freebusy only)
- Friend search &lt;1s, invitations 7-day expiry
- Algorithm &lt;500ms, top rec 70% when majority free
- Nudges max 2x/week, opt-out per group/global
